Sediment_Collection_Depth_cm: 1-3 cm as described in the protocol
Additional_Sampling_Notes: 90-95% of stream in area covered by snow. Labeled filter only used for 3 ICR samples, water in the needle froze after completing the 2nd replicate. Labeled filter preserved and new filter and needle used for rest of filtered samples. DO sensor placement, all water sampling, and some sediment sampling performed on depositional zone on the inside of a channel bend. Additional sediment gathered about 20 m downstream from the lip of a pool. Right before shipping (taking out of the refrigerator), frost was observed on ziploc bags and bulk water samples felt frozen in their bottles.

MiniDot_Notes: Right before dam, on side channel off of the main. Site located in a park near the boat ramp, with some but not heavy human presence impact. Mostly fishing/hunting, not a spot for swimming, etc. A boat did launch nearby around 16:40 and disturbed the sensor a little. The nearby shoreline was pretty steep with a drop off- not great for sampling.
Additional_Sampling_Notes: Potential impact from boat launch, site on side channel with a decent amount of fish, insect, and bird presence, just upstream from a major dam. There was no exposed soil along the bank, it was all vegetated (e.g., CM_115-exposed).
